SAIC Group to Inject Assets Into Listed Units, News Reports

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-02-13T12:49:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-13/saic-group-to-inject-assets-into-listed-units-news-reports.html
Shanghai Automotive Industry Corp.
(Group) will incorporate its remaining automotive and certain
service assets into its SAIC Motor Corp., Shanghai Securities
News reported on its website yesterday, citing unidentified
officials with knowledge of the plan. It did not elaborate.  The group company plans to inject the “remaining
autoparts” assets into another unit, Huayu Automotive Systems
Co., the newspaper reported. Shares of Shanghai-listed SAIC
Motor and Huayu Automotive will be suspended from trading on
Monday pending an announcement over their parent’s plan related
to the companies, they said in separate statements on Feb. 11.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 rdobson4@bloomberg.net  